{
  "text": "Th e World Health Organization estimates that nearly 1 million people die from suicide yearly (World Health Organization figures, 2012). Psychological autopsies find that about 90% of suicides in Western nations have a psychiatric illness at the time of suicide. [CITATION_1] Of those, about 60% are suffering from a mood disorder. Suicide risk is influenced by a wide range of factors. Although some genetic risk factors have been identified, environmental events such as childhood adversity or repeated exposure to life-threatening situations typical in war and active combat have also been reported to contribute to the increased risk of suicidal behavior.",
